'''ISO 7027:1999''' is an [[ISO]] standard for [[water quality]] that enables the determination of [[turbidity]].<ref>ISO 7027:1999 -
Water quality -- Determination of turbidity http://www.iso.org/iso/catalogue_detail.htm?csnumber=30123</ref> The ISO 7027 technique is used to determine the [[concentration]] of suspended particles in a sample of water by measuring the incident light scattered at right angles from the sample. The scattered light is captured by a [[photodiode]], which produces an electronic signal that is converted to a [[turbidity]].

