{{Infobox power station | name = Langley Park Wind Farm | image = | image_caption = | location_map = County Durham | coordinates = {{coord|54.795|-1.6672|region:GB_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | name_official = | country = [[England]], [[United Kingdom]] | location = [[Langley Park, County Durham]] | status = Operational | construction_began = | commissioned = December 2008 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[EDF Energy]] | operator = Cumbria Wind Farms | ps_units_operational = 4 × 2.05 MW | ps_units_manu_model = REpower Systems: MM82 | wind_hub_height = 59m | wind_rotor_diameter = 82m | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = | wind_site_elevation = 1552 ft | wind_site_usage = | wind_offshore_depth = | wind_offshore_distance = | ps_electrical_capacity = 8.2 MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = }}
'''Langley Park Wind Farm''' is a [[wind farm]] near [[Langley Park, County Durham|Langley Park]], [[County Durham]], [[England]]. It was developed by [[EDF Energy]] and is operated by [[Cumbria Wind Farms]], the farm has a [[Intermittent energy source#Terminology|nameplate capacity]] of 8.2 [[Megawatt|MW]], containing four REpower Systems' MM82 [[Wind turbine|turbines]] each rated at 2.05MW.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bwea.com/ukwed/operational.asp |title=RenewableUK |first=RenewableUK |last=Association |publisher= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102132011/http://www.bwea.com/ukwed/operational.asp |archivedate=2012-11-02 |df= }}</ref>
In 2008 EDF accepted that it had failed to check the impact of the turbines on [[Freeview (UK)|digital television]] reception, after residents of villages where the turbines lay on a line-of-site to the local TV transmitter complained of a loss of signal strength and severe Freeview Digital Services disruption, particularly when the turbine blades rotate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/north-east-news/todays-evening-chronicle/2008/11/06/company-admits-wind-farms-ruined-tv-reception-72703-22196802/|title=Company admits wind farms ruined TV reception|first=Kerry|last=Wood|date=6 November 2008|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://freespace.virgin.net/lawrie.milner/digitaltv/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-03-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100328121400/http://freespace.virgin.net/lawrie.milner/digitaltv/ |archivedate=2010-03-28 |df= }}</ref>
