{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} {{chembox | verifiedrevid = 428749498 | Name = Potassium aluminium borate | ImageFile = <!-- | ImageSize = 200px --> | ImageName = Potassium aluminium borate | OtherNames = | Section1 = {{Chembox Identifiers | InChI=1/2Al.B2O7.2K/c;;3-1(4,5)9-2(6,7)8;;/q2*+3;-8;2*+1 }} | Section2 = {{Chembox Properties | Formula =K<sub>2</sub>Al<sub>2</sub>B<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub> | MolarMass = | Density = | Solvent = | SolubleOther = | MeltingPt = | BoilingPt = }} }} '''Potassium aluminium borate''' (K<sub>2</sub>Al<sub>2</sub>B<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub>) is an [[ionic compound]] composed of potassium ions, aluminium ions, and [[borate]] ions. Its crystal form exhibits [[nonlinear optics|nonlinear optical properties]]. The [[ultraviolet]] beam at 266&nbsp;nm can be obtained by fourth [[harmonic generation]] (FGH) of 1064&nbsp;nm [[Nd:YAG]] laser radiation through a nonlinear crystal K<sub>2</sub>Al<sub>2</sub>B<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub> (KABO).
