{{Infobox lake | name = San Antonio Reservoir | image = | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Alameda County, California]] | coords = {{coord|37.58118|N|121.82825|W|region:US-CA_type:waterbody_source:placeopedia|display=inline,title}} | type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = [[San Antonio Creek (Alameda County)|San Antonio Creek]] | outflow = [[San Antonio Creek (Alameda County)|San Antonio Creek]] | catchment = | basin_countries = United States | length = | width = | area = | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | cities = }} '''San Antonio Reservoir''' is located in [[Alameda County, California]], about three miles east-southeast of [[Sunol, California|Sunol]]. It was built in 1964<ref name=DWR /> by the City and County of [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]]. Formed by the '''James H. Turner Dam'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.water.ca.gov/damsafety/docs/Reservoir2010.pdf|title=Dams With a Different Reservoir Name|publisher=California Department of Water Resources|accessdate=October 15, 2012}}</ref> across [[San Antonio Creek (Alameda Creek)|San Antonio Creek]]<ref name=DWR>{{Cite web|url=http://www.water.ca.gov/damsafety/docs/Juris(H-M)2010.pdf|title=Dams Within the Jurisdiction of the State of California|publisher=California Department of Water Resources|accessdate=October 15, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121005023236/http://www.water.ca.gov/damsafety/docs/Juris%28H-M%292010.pdf|archivedate=October 5, 2012|df=}}</ref> not far above where it flows into [[Alameda Creek]], its purpose is to store water from the [[Hetch Hetchy Aqueduct]] and local [[water well|wells]] and [[drainage basin|watersheds]]. It has a capacity of {{convert|50,500|acre.ft|m3|lk=in}}.<ref name=DWR />
The reservoir is not open to the public.
